14:10.549 --> 14:12.865
Oh, come on.
That's not fair.

14:12.867 --> 14:14.134
Ah, hot soup!

14:14.136 --> 14:16.703
Hot soup.

14:18.139 --> 14:20.173
Thank you.
Look, Walden,

14:20.175 --> 14:21.558
I agreed to have dinner with you

14:21.560 --> 14:23.476
because I care about you,
but I just...

14:23.478 --> 14:25.228
Are we going to have sex later?

14:25.230 --> 14:26.646
Let me finish.

14:26.648 --> 14:27.981
But no.

14:27.983 --> 14:29.882
Aw.

14:29.884 --> 14:32.185
The thing is,
even though I care about you,

14:32.187 --> 14:34.020
this marriage is over.

14:34.022 --> 14:35.605
I don't want to get
a divorce.

14:35.607 --> 14:37.657
Why do we got to get a divorce?

14:37.659 --> 14:38.775
Because I have grown up

14:38.777 --> 14:41.077
and you are still the same guy
you were at 19.

14:41.079 --> 14:42.112
No, that is not true.

14:42.114 --> 14:43.246
I got a lot more money now.

14:43.248 --> 14:44.497
Money isn't the point.

14:44.499 --> 14:46.082
I got lawyers,
I got accountants,

14:46.084 --> 14:47.900
I got my own
charitable foundation.

14:47.902 --> 14:50.337
It's not about what you have;
it's about who you are.

14:50.339 --> 14:51.504
Oh.

14:51.506 --> 14:53.757
Well, I'm pretty much
the same guy.

14:53.759 --> 14:56.543
What I want, what I need,
is a partner in life.

14:56.545 --> 15:00.096
A grown-up, mature,
responsible adult.

15:00.098 --> 15:01.464
What, and you don't think
that's me?

15:01.466 --> 15:02.915
No, I don't.

15:05.436 --> 15:06.919
And you don't think
I can change?

15:06.921 --> 15:08.221
No, I don't.
But what if I can?

15:08.223 --> 15:09.272
But you can't.
Can, too.

15:09.274 --> 15:10.807
Just eat your dinner.

15:13.311 --> 15:14.728
Ugh.

15:14.730 --> 15:15.946
This blows.

15:15.948 --> 15:17.530
I know, but it's something

15:17.532 --> 15:19.783
we're both just going
to have to accept.

15:21.369 --> 15:23.436
How's your beach house?

15:23.438 --> 15:25.622
It's okay.

15:26.657 --> 15:27.991
But I miss you.

15:27.993 --> 15:29.993
I miss you, too, sometimes.

15:29.995 --> 15:30.961
Really?

15:30.963 --> 15:33.046
Walden, we were together
for 15 years.

15:33.048 --> 15:35.298
Those feelings
don't just go away.

15:38.637 --> 15:41.805
Hey, be cool.

15:42.923 --> 15:46.125
So, uh, you really still have
feelings for me?

15:46.127 --> 15:48.511
Of course I do.
Oh.

15:49.798 --> 15:51.264
Hey.

15:51.266 --> 15:53.817
Big girls don't throw food.

15:55.403 --> 15:57.737
Trust me, I can change.

15:57.739 --> 15:59.305
I really can.

16:01.410 --> 16:02.492
All right, that's it.
Eat lettuce!

16:02.494 --> 16:05.195
Walden!
What? She started it.

16:05.197 --> 16:06.329
Whoa! No pasta.

16:06.331 --> 16:07.781
I call no pasta.

16:10.402 --> 16:11.818
Oh, it is on!

16:12.670 --> 16:13.920
Oh, yeah.

16:13.922 --> 16:15.705
And she got some...
Here it comes.

16:15.707 --> 16:17.040
Here it comes.
Here it comes.

16:18.126 --> 16:20.093
♪ Men. ♪

16:21.797 --> 16:23.513
Berta, can you
get the door?

16:23.515 --> 16:25.965
I'm off the clock, Zippy.

16:25.967 --> 16:27.801
What clock?
You're a live-in.

16:27.803 --> 16:30.103
And I'm livin'.

16:35.443 --> 16:38.662
You know you took
the wrong brother, right?

16:40.347 --> 16:41.731
Judith, what are
you doing here?

16:41.733 --> 16:43.320
Why did you tell Jake
he could quit school?

16:43.368 --> 16:44.320
I didn't.

16:44.345 --> 16:45.616
Well, then, where
did he get the idea?

16:45.620 --> 16:47.570
Walden. He told him
about how when he quit

16:47.572 --> 16:49.021
he made hundreds of
millions of dollars,

16:49.023 --> 16:50.957
and now Jake thinks
he can do it, too.

16:50.959 --> 16:52.542
Terrific.
And I thought your brother

16:52.544 --> 16:54.044
was a horrible influence.

16:54.046 --> 16:55.745
Don't speak ill
of the dead.

16:55.747 --> 16:58.331
But you're right-- he was
a terrible human being.

16:58.333 --> 17:01.084
Hey, who's at
the... Whoops!

17:01.086 --> 17:03.803
You come back
here, young man!

17:04.805 --> 17:06.388
He's not coming back, is he?

17:06.391 --> 17:08.223
I wouldn't.

17:09.209 --> 17:10.643
Hey.

17:10.645 --> 17:12.929
Walden, I want a word with you.

17:12.931 --> 17:14.897
Walden, you remember
Judith. Bye.

17:17.401 --> 17:18.734
You're Alan's ex, right?

17:18.737 --> 17:20.603
Yes, and Jake's mother.

17:20.605 --> 17:22.188
And you and I need
to discuss how...

17:22.190 --> 17:23.573
I just had dinner
with my ex.

17:23.575 --> 17:24.891
Well, that's very
nice. Anyway...

17:24.893 --> 17:26.492
She's not my ex yet,
but she's going to be.

17:26.494 --> 17:27.743
I'm sorry.

17:27.746 --> 17:30.580
She hates me,
but I'm still in love with her.

17:30.582 --> 17:33.450
Well, I'm sure you'll find
somebody else.

17:34.869 --> 17:38.404
Since we were teenagers,
she's been the only one.

17:38.406 --> 17:40.256
You were high school
sweethearts?

17:40.258 --> 17:42.459
Yeah.

17:45.296 --> 17:47.514
That is so romantic.

17:52.136 --> 17:55.271
And I blew it again tonight.

17:55.273 --> 17:56.756
Oh. Hey, come on now.

17:56.758 --> 17:58.224
It... it'll be okay.

17:58.226 --> 18:00.944
No, it'll never be okay.

18:02.279 --> 18:04.280
She's my soul mate.

18:04.282 --> 18:07.734
Oh, you poor,
sweet man.

18:09.069 --> 18:12.572
Who smells like ranch dressing
and fettuccine alfredo.

18:13.457 --> 18:15.492
Have you ever loved
anyone like that?

18:16.827 --> 18:18.628
No.

18:18.630 --> 18:21.164
Don't, 'cause it
hurts too much.

18:21.166 --> 18:23.466
Oh, I wish there was
something I could do.

18:23.468 --> 18:25.385
Like what?

18:37.698 --> 18:39.849
Oh, yeah,
I'm so quitting high school.

18:39.851 --> 18:42.101
♪ Men. ♪

18:46.338 --> 18:47.404
♪ Men. ♪

18:47.406 --> 18:48.972
For the last time, Jake,

18:48.974 --> 18:50.924
you're not dropping out
of high school.

18:50.926 --> 18:53.360
What if I can convince Mom
to let me?

18:53.362 --> 18:54.895
Sure.

18:54.897 --> 18:58.365
If your mother says it's okay,
you can have my blessing.

18:59.200 --> 19:01.434
Cool.

19:01.436 --> 19:04.404
And while I'm at it,
I'll buy you a car.

19:05.284 --> 19:07.669
Oh, no, no, a space ship.

19:08.210 --> 19:09.990
Car's fine.

19:09.991 --> 19:11.157
Good night, Jake.

19:11.159 --> 19:12.425
Good night, Dad.

19:15.463 --> 19:17.630
That...
that was the air mattress.

19:17.632 --> 19:19.365
Okay.

19:24.037 --> 19:25.938
That was me.

19:29.627 --> 19:31.627
Holy moly.

19:31.629 --> 19:33.763
What got into
you tonight?

19:33.765 --> 19:36.732
You know,
besides <i>moi.</i>

19:37.985 --> 19:39.435
Shh. Don't talk.

19:39.437 --> 19:41.070
Okay.

19:44.462 --> 19:46.462
How would you feel
about growing a beard?

19:47.908 --> 19:49.358
Wouldn't that
scratch your face?

19:51.179 --> 19:52.511
Yeah.

